This code creates a c++ version and also adds a mex wrapper

Original examples:
without makefile
g++ curve2.cpp lmlib/lmcurve.cpp lmlib/lmmin.cpp -Ilmlib -lm -o curve2
g++ curve2.cpp Optimizer_class.cpp lmlib/lmcurve.cpp lmlib/lmmin.cpp -Ilmlib -o curve2

Current method for compiling the three main versions:

Orton:
mex curve2mex_OrtonOff.cpp Optimizer_class.cpp ToftsOrtonOffset.cpp ToftsOrton.cpp ToftsWeinOffset.cpp ToftsWeinOffsetVp.cpp lmlib/lmcurve.cpp lmlib/lmmin.cpp -Ilmlib

Weinmann
mex curve2mex_WeinOff.cpp Optimizer_class.cpp ToftsOrtonOffset.cpp ToftsOrton.cpp ToftsWeinOffset.cpp ToftsWeinOffsetVp.cpp lmlib/lmcurve.cpp lmlib/lmmin.cpp -Ilmlib

Weinmann with vp fit
mex curve2mex_WeinOffVp.cpp Optimizer_class.cpp ToftsOrtonOffset.cpp ToftsOrton.cpp ToftsWeinOffset.cpp ToftsWeinOffsetVp.cpp lmlib/lmcurve.cpp lmlib/lmmin.cpp -Ilmlib

Try:
Testing_function.m
